cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using speech and language to predict behavior in cancer-afflicted patient and spouse interactions. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper deals with analyzing turn-level acoustic speech patterns. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper deals with interpersonal communication attributes. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper deals with improving communication between cancer patients and their spouse caregivers. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper deals with the impact of cancer on the quality of life of patients and their caregivers.
